`TrackedArray` wraps a native array and makes all mutation methods (`.push()`, `.pop()`, `.splice()`, etc.) reactive. Import it from `tracked-built-ins`. Note that `bowlers` itself does not need `@tracked` — the `TrackedArray` instance handles reactivity internally for all mutations.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { TrackedObject } from 'tracked-built-ins';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

export default class PlayerStatsComponent extends Component {
  stats = new TrackedObject({
    runs: 0,
